x4freetext: 16O(G.P) REACTION FOR EG = 100 - 400 MEV.

x4codes.hlp: Massachusetts Institute of Technology, Cambridge, MA, United States of America

x4freetext: THE 4HE GAS WAS CONTAINED IN A CYLINDRICAL CELL OF
DIAMETER 7.6 CM AND HEIGHT 6.2 CM WITH 0.03 MM THICK
ELGILOY MATAL WALLS. WITH THE BEAM ON THE TARGET THE
GAS TEMPERATURE WAS ABOUT 34 K AND THE PRESSURE WAS
900 MEV/C MAGNETIC SPECTROMETER.
THE (G,P) CROSS SECTIONS LEADING TO THE 15N GROUND AND
FIRST THREE EXCITED STATES WERE EXTRACTED BY FITTING
THE MEASURED PHOTOPROTON ENERGY SPECTRA WITH A
CALCULATED SPECTRUM CONTAINING THE (UNKNOWN) CROSS
SECTIONS AND THE (KNOWN) BREMSSTRAHLUNG SPECTRUM.
CROSS SECTION OBTAINED FROM THE FITS OF MEASURED
PHOTOPROTON ENERGY SPECTRA WERE CORRECTED FOR DEAD
TIME LOSSES.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: THE ERRORS QUOTED ARE THE STATISTICAL
UNCERTAINTIES COMBINED WITH AN ENERGY-DEPENDENT
ERROR WHICH VARIES FROM 1.7 % FOR EG < 151 MEV TO
9 % AT EG = 380 MEV DUE TO THE UNCERTAINTY IN THE
CORRECTION FOR NUCLEAR INTERACTIONS OF THE PROTONS
IN THE PLASTIC SCINTILLATOR AND IRON ABSORBERS. IN
ADDITION, THERE ARE SYSTEMATIC UNCERTAINTIES OF
ABOUT 4 % AND 3 %, ARISING FROM UNCERTAINTIES IN
THE INCIDENT PHOTON FLUX AND DEAD TIME CORRECTION,
RESPECTIVELY.
THE DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTION FOR 16O(G,P)15N
PROCESS HAS BEEN MEASURED IN THE ENERGY RANGE EG =
100 - 400 MEV AT LABORATORY ANGLES OF 45, 90, AND
135 DEGREE. THE CROSS SECTIONS FOR THE (G,P)
REACTIONS LEAVING 15N IN ITS GROUND STATE, IN ITS
FIRST AND SECOND EXCITED STATES AT E-EXC ABOUT 5.3
MEV, AND IN ITS THIRD EXCITED STATE AT E-EXC = 6.3
MEV WERE EXTRACTED FROM THE TIP REGION OF THE PROTON
SPECTRA MEASURED AT A SERIES OF BREMSSTRAHLUNG
END-POINT ENERGIES. THE DATA WERE COMPARED WITH
CALCULATIONS BASED ON A DIRECT, SINGLE-PARTICLE
KNOCKOUT MECHANISM AND ON MECHANISMS INVOLVING TWO
PARTICLES IN THE INTERMEDIATE STATE.
DATA FROM THE TABLES 1 - 3.
DATA WERE COMPILED AT THE USA BNL NNDC BY
V.V.VARLAMOV.
